00:36:15.360 --> 00:36:19.640
&gt;&gt;Male #1: Whatís the trick to the split
shot?

00:36:19.640 --> 00:36:22.420
&gt;&gt;Cheng: Whatís the trick to the split shot?
The trick is to use a large dome port. The

00:36:22.420 --> 00:36:28.930
more surface area you have, the less chop
in the water will affect the shot. Itís also

00:36:28.930 --> 00:36:34.220
toóDepending on the material and how old
the dome port is, water will sheet differently.

00:36:34.220 --> 00:36:39.450
These shots were almost all taken with water
completely covering the dome port. I dipped

00:36:39.450 --> 00:36:45.890
the dome in the water, and I pulled it out
of the water. Before it beads, I take a picture.

00:36:45.890 --> 00:36:50.330
Some people have managed to figure out ways
with their dome ports to make it completelyó

00:36:50.330 --> 00:36:51.330
&gt;&gt;Male #1: {inaudible}

00:36:51.330 --> 00:36:55.080
&gt;&gt;Cheng: The coating isóPeople use spit,
and they use baby shampoo sometimes. Iíve

00:36:55.080 --> 00:37:00.180
seen {raynecks} attempted, which does not
work because it beads most of the water off,

00:37:00.180 --> 00:37:05.070
but then it leaves lots of little beads, which
show up. I find that the way Iíve been most

00:37:05.070 --> 00:37:09.980
successful is by using clean glass dome ports
that have not been etched by diesel. Diesel

00:37:09.980 --> 00:37:14.800
will etch these dome ports if you leave them
in the bottom of the tender of a boat. The

00:37:14.800 --> 00:37:19.690
water in there has some gas and some fuel
in it. That, I found, has been pretty disruptive

00:37:19.690 --> 00:37:22.060
to glass. There are a lot of tricks.

00:37:22.060 --> 00:37:23.160
&gt;&gt;Male #8: Why not acrylic?

00:37:23.160 --> 00:37:26.850
&gt;&gt;Cheng: Why not acrylic? I just havenít
had as much luck with acrylic. I feel like

00:37:26.850 --> 00:37:32.270
it doesnít sheet as well for some reason.
Iím not sure why. Maybe a brand new acrylic

00:37:32.270 --> 00:37:37.260
port thatís super smooth could do it. You
can get them with both. The best way is just

00:37:37.260 --> 00:37:41.490
to keep it dry. Keep the top half dry if you
can. If itís totally smooth water, you can

00:37:41.490 --> 00:37:46.280
dry it off and then be very careful about
your shot. But very often, weíre floating,

00:37:46.280 --> 00:37:49.930
and just come up from a dive, and youíre
shooting a split. So you have to work with

00:37:49.930 --> 00:37:57.440
what you have. [pause] [man coughs]
This is another whale shark, another split

00:37:57.440 --> 00:38:05.520
of a whale shark shot. This is a whale shark
feeding. Itís in Isla Mujeres in the Gulf

00:38:05.520 --> 00:38:10.380
of Mexico, just off the Yucat·n. This is
happening right now. In fact, Wetpixel has

