00:43:02.550 --> 00:43:08.420
well protected, so if you want to get in the
water with a whale, you have to be on permit.

00:43:08.420 --> 00:43:14.641
We use hydrophones to find these whales. Sperm
whales make a lot of noise. They click. They

00:43:14.641 --> 00:43:19.960
have, in fact, a coda for just certain populations,
so you can tell which population of whales

00:43:19.960 --> 00:43:26.210
from by the pattern that they use to greet
each other. They use very loud noises at depth,

00:43:26.210 --> 00:43:30.940
1000 meters down when they feed. They have
specific feeding noises, and so you can track

00:43:30.940 --> 00:43:36.780
them as they move around on their dives, which
