Yeah. Other questions?

00:49:06.740 --> 00:49:13.821
&gt;&gt;Male #12: I want to know about the radio
triggers for the flash.

00:49:13.821 --> 00:49:20.250
&gt;&gt;Cheng: Radio triggers for the flash? We
donít use radio triggers. We use either electrical

00:49:20.250 --> 00:49:30.400
sync cords or optical sync. You have to trigger
the camera somehow. For a while, when digital

00:49:30.400 --> 00:49:35.280
cameras came out, underwater photographers
lost the ability to use TTL, because everyóThat

00:49:35.280 --> 00:49:40.460
went D-TTL and i-TTL, and Canon went E-TTL.
And none of the underwater strobe manufacturers

00:49:40.460 --> 00:49:45.140
could catch up. So we shotóAnd thatís when
I started shooting. So we pretty much shot

00:49:45.140 --> 00:49:48.710
manual. Everything was manual.
But I find, in general, all you need is a

00:49:48.710 --> 00:49:53.460
signal to fire the strobe, because if you
rely on TTL, especially for macro, and you

00:49:53.460 --> 00:49:58.270
have more than one strobe, the pictures end
up looking really flat. The idea is to think

00:49:58.270 --> 00:50:03.790
about shadows. Shadows are the most important
thing for underwater macrophotography. You

00:50:03.790 --> 00:50:08.390
always want to think about where that shadowís
going to be cast. Since so many animals underwater

00:50:08.390 --> 00:50:13.660
are totally camouflaged, the best way to cut
them out of the environment is to make them

00:50:13.660 --> 00:50:15.500
cast a shadow on their host.

00:50:15.500 --> 00:50:18.220
&gt;&gt;Male #13: So youíreó

00:50:18.220 --> 00:50:20.950
&gt;&gt;Cheng: Oh, go ahead.

00:50:20.950 --> 00:50:27.490
&gt;&gt;Male #13: What do you think is your most
dangerous encounter ever? Anything youíve

00:50:27.490 --> 00:50:28.490
ever been close to?

00:50:28.490 --> 00:50:30.290
&gt;&gt;Cheng: [laughs] My most dangerous encounter
ever? I donít think my most dangerous encounters

00:50:30.290 --> 00:50:36.040
have been wildlife related. [laughter] Itís
mostly been in a situation where youíre in

00:50:36.040 --> 00:50:40.790
a very high current environment and youíve
pushed yourself somehow. Iím too deep, Iím

00:50:40.790 --> 00:50:44.510
in deco, I donít have much air left, and
all I can see are my bubbles streaming off

00:50:44.510 --> 00:50:50.060
into the blue when Iím ready to let go to
go do a safety stop where you drift for three

00:50:50.060 --> 00:50:54.760
to five minutes, plus deco time. So there
have been some moments like that that are

00:50:54.760 --> 00:50:59.510
very visceral memories where Iímómy back
is to the current, and Iím just staring at

00:50:59.510 --> 00:51:03.780
my bubbles going down, and thinking, ìOkay,
