00:51:03.780 --> 00:51:07.040
me.î
So there were some moments like that. Luckily,

00:51:07.040 --> 00:51:11.390
Iíve never had anything truly life-threatening.
I think most of my friends who have been doing

00:51:11.390 --> 00:51:16.400
this for a long time have been bent or have
had some kind of serious malfunction. Their

00:51:16.400 --> 00:51:24.131
first stage blows off their tank or something
really disastrous. The only realóThe only

00:51:24.131 --> 00:51:30.880
lethal incidents, at least, amongst my friends,
have involved rebreathers. They have a rebreather

00:51:30.880 --> 00:51:36.100
accident and they die. Or the occasional surf
photographer can get smashed in the coral.

00:51:36.100 --> 00:51:40.670
So there are just a fewóSometimes, there
are really unfortunate events, especially

00:51:40.670 --> 00:51:44.480
rebreather stuff. Even really experienced
rebreather divers can have accidents like

00:51:44.480 --> 00:51:47.300
that. Itís less forgiving than open circuit.
[pause]

00:51:47.300 --> 00:51:48.470
Other questions?

00:51:48.470 --> 00:51:53.880
&gt;&gt;Male #1: So have you done much rebreather
diving at all?

00:51:53.880 --> 00:51:57.550
&gt;&gt;Cheng: Iíve done some rebreather diving.
I donít own one, but I typically will dive

00:51:57.550 --> 00:52:01.480
it in Papua New Guinea where thereís a boat
that I go on that has them.

00:52:01.480 --> 00:52:03.900
&gt;&gt;Male #1: Why is that? Why only there?

00:52:03.900 --> 00:52:06.360
&gt;&gt;Cheng: Itís mostly that I just donít own
one. I havenít invested in one.

00:52:06.360 --> 00:52:09.170
&gt;&gt;Male #1: And you think theyíre dangerous.

00:52:09.170 --> 00:52:12.880
&gt;&gt;Cheng: Well, I think if you donít use them
a lot, if youíre not very comfortable with

00:52:12.880 --> 00:52:17.710
them, they can be dangerous. I love them.
I mean, rebreathers, for those of you who

00:52:17.710 --> 00:52:22.950
donít know, are fully closed circuits, so
they scrub the CO2 out of what you exhale,

00:52:22.950 --> 00:52:30.050
and inject a very small amount of oxygen into
the system. Itís bubble-free. Almost everything

00:52:30.050 --> 00:52:35.650
underwater is afraid of bubbles. If you ever
go underwater and hold your breath or are

00:52:35.650 --> 00:52:40.530
on a rebreather, divers make a ton of noise.
You can hear divers long before you can see

00:52:40.530 --> 00:52:45.330
them, in the water. It affects the wildlife.
You can immediately see the fish start hiding.

00:52:45.330 --> 00:52:49.180
With every exhalation, if you have someone
on scuba whoís taking video, you can watch

00:52:49.180 --> 00:52:53.760
the fish pulse in and out as they breathe.
With a rebreather, you just donít see that.

00:52:53.760 --> 00:52:58.260
And the other benefit of using a rebreather
for photography and videography is that as

00:52:58.260 --> 00:53:02.200
you breathe, your buoyancy does not change,
because thereís a counterlung. You exhale

00:53:02.200 --> 00:53:06.370
into the counterlung, so the amount of air
stays constant. With open circuit, every time

00:53:06.370 --> 00:53:10.890
